    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-29T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-29T13:00:00-05:00" n="867"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d867">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.51 Frozen Credits 25/42: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-29T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 29, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2011. The economic project containing controls legislation, see my telegram 1892,
                    November 4, 7 p.m.,<note n="32" xml:id="d867fn32">Not printed.</note> was voted
                    on in the Chamber of Deputies on November 23 after having been voted out of the
                    Senate on November 17. The final result was that Senate and lower house approved
                    all except some half dozen provisions and most of last week was occupied in
                    determining whether differences should be resolved by a mixed commission of both
                    houses under article LI of the Constitution. Notwithstanding considerable
                    opposition the project was transmitted directly to the President of the Republic
                    Saturday, omitting the articles not agreed on, but it is reported that the
                    President may veto certain sections respecting increased salary scales of
                    Government employees before signing the measure. It therefore appears likely
                    that project and with it the controls legislation may be promulgated as a law
                    this week or the early part of the ensuing week.<note n="33" xml:id="d867fn33"
                        >The President and his Ministers signed the decree promulgating the Economic
                        Project legislation on December 22, 1943.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
